annotationA: cGMP-dependent protein kinase, isozyme 2 forms cD4/T1/T3A/T3B; Foraging (For) is a serine/threonine kinase and a member of the Protein Kinase G (PKG) family. For roles include feeding, locomotion, metabolism, development, olfactory habituation, learning and memory, stress, social behavior, as well as Malpighian tubule, heart, muscle and synaptic function
annotationB: 6-pyruvoyl tetrahydrobiopterin synthase; Required for pigment and biopterin synthesis; Belongs to the PTPS family
